## 1. Face Detection Pipeline — 15 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (13–15) | Good (10–12) | Adequate (7–9) | Poor (0–6) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Model selection & justification** | Uses a modern detector (RetinaFace, SCRFD, YOLOv8-face) with clear justification referencing benchmarks (e.g. WIDER FACE AP). Compares ≥2 detectors. | Uses an appropriate detector (e.g. MTCNN or RetinaFace) with brief justification. | Uses a single off-the-shelf detector with no comparative analysis. | No deep-learning detector; or detector does not produce bounding boxes. |
| **Bounding box accuracy** | Tight bounding boxes on all team members under varying lighting and distance; handles partial occlusion. | Bounding boxes present and mostly accurate; occasional misses on profile/occluded faces. | Bounding boxes present but noticeably inaccurate or miss small faces. | Bounding boxes missing or consistently wrong. |
| **Real-time capability** | ≥ 20 FPS on demo hardware; latency metrics reported. | 10–19 FPS; minor perceptible lag. | 5–9 FPS; noticeable lag but still usable. | < 5 FPS or not real-time. |

---

## 2. Face Recognition & Embedding Quality — 20 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (17–20) | Good (13–16) | Adequate (9–12) | Poor (0–8) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Model depth & understanding** | Uses a strong backbone (ResNet-100, ViT, or FaceLiVT) trained with angular margin loss (ArcFace / AdaFace). Demonstrates understanding of embedding space geometry. | Uses FaceNet or a pre-trained InsightFace model; explains embedding concept. | Uses a pre-trained model as a black box; minimal explanation. | No recognition model or classifier-only approach with no embeddings. |
| **Open-set "Unknown" handling** | Implements a calibrated similarity threshold with justification; demonstrates low false-positive rate for unseen faces. | Has a threshold-based unknown signal; tested with ≥2 unknown subjects. | "Unknown" label exists but threshold is arbitrary or untested. | No unknown detection. |
| **Fine-tuning / advanced work** *(bonus-eligible)* | Fine-tunes on collected data or trains a custom model on VGGFace2/WebFace; reports before/after metrics. | Attempts fine-tuning with partial results. | Uses only pre-trained weights. | N/A (no penalty, but no bonus). |

