## 5. Technical Report — 15 pts

| Criterion | Excellent (13–15) | Good (10–12) | Adequate (7–9) | Poor (0–6) |
|-----------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------|------------|
| **Architecture description** | Clear pipeline diagram; explains each stage (detection → alignment → embedding → matching); cites relevant papers. | Describes the pipeline with some detail; references present. | High-level description only; few or no references. | No architecture description. |
| **Performance analysis** | Reports quantitative metrics (accuracy, FPS, ROC/DET curves, threshold analysis); compares with baselines. | Reports accuracy and FPS; limited analysis. | Reports only pass/fail observations. | No metrics. |
| **Individual contributions** | Clearly delineated per-member contributions; signed by all members. | Contributions listed but vaguely described. | Contributions section present but incomplete. | Missing contributions or signatures. |
| **Writing quality** | Well-structured, professional, free of major errors. | Readable with minor issues. | Disorganized or hard to follow. | Incomprehensible or largely copy-pasted. |

